I know that social media is supposed to be for flaunting your health, and wealth.. but I'm a little different. I have an invisible illness that causes me so much pain some days that sometimes getting from the bed to the couch is a real accomplishment.

For 15 years, I've had more tests run, needles poked, ice packs applied in my early years than people twice my age. I've asked doctors for a replacement body, because I think mine is defective.. Not to mention super pricey! 😝

My only ask, please don't judge a person who doesn't "look sick, " because there is no once-size-fits all struggle with chronic illness. You never know what they're going through. Be kind. 🦋

I am a #spoonie. Every day I just try to show up, and never give up.

#chronicillness #chronicpain #spoonies #sick #illness #chronicpainawareness
 #chronicpainwarrior #pain #motivation #mondaymotivation #survival #sick #chronicpainsucks
